				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$|f^\mathrm {L}_\mathrm {V}V_{tb}|^{2}$$\end{document} [4, 5], i.e. depends on the coupling between the W boson, top and b quarks. The tW channel, represented in Fig. 1, has a pp production cross-section at s=13TeV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
