				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$R=0.4$$\end{document}. Particle-level jet b-tagging is performed by checking the jets for any associated b-hadron with pT>5GeV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$p_{\text {T}} >5~\hbox {GeV}$$\end{document}. This association is achieved by reclustering jets with b-hadrons included in the input list of particles, but with their pT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
