				\begin{document}$$\Delta _i$$\end{document} is the width of bin i of the particle-level distribution. Differential cross-sections are divided by the fiducial cross-section to create a normalised distribution. The fiducial cross-section is simply the sum of the cross-sections in each bin multiplied by the corresponding bin widths:σfid=∑idσidX·Δi=∑iNiufdL.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
