				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$E(\ell \ell b)$$\end{document} distribution, where the lower p values for all MC predictions reflect this. In most cases, differences between the MC predictions are smaller than the uncertainty on the data, but there are some signs that Powheg-Box +Herwig++ deviates more from the data and from the other predictions in certain bins of the E(ℓℓb)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
